OrderRequestHeader.Comments:
Order Request cXML only supported only one Comments element at Header level and one Comments element at Item level however it is very often that each Order will have multiple texts at Header and Item level that need to be communicated to suppliers. Such multiple comments are currently being managed with extriniscs by customers. With cXML 45 enhancements, repeatability for Comments at Order Request Header and Item are supported so that multiple comments are supported in the standard cXML without having to use extrinsics or concatenation.
In addition, Order Request cXML does not support identification of Order Items that are relevant for Kanban, if Item has Unlimited delivery tolerance specified and cXML 45 enhancements provide standard intrinsics to support these attributes.
Additionally, existing extrinsic to indicate if a PO item has changed is converted to intrinsic 'IsItemChanged'.
All the above enhancement will be done to support cXML 45 enhancements for Order Request cXML
